CONDITIONS MODIFIED ON 06/03/2022:  If DNA sample has not been taken from the defendant, the Court orders sample to be taken;  and it may be expunged under 165.77(4) Wis. Statutes.  Defendant to have no contact with Victim A (or their residence in which they occupy during the pendency of the case)/Witness A listed in the Criminal Complaint/Victim Identification Key.  Defendant is not to share, reproduce or distribute any personal and/or identifying information about the crime victim(s), except to their attorney.  Defendant to report/comply with Wisconsin Community Services Pretrial Supervision Program under Level 4 supervision.  Defendant to comply with GPS monitoring through Wisconsin Community Services.  Defendant is not to come within 1 mile of Victim A, listed in the Victim Identification Key, or their residence, employment, school or anywhere they frequent.  The Defendant to pay all costs associated with GPS. The Defendant to report to WCS within 1 business day of being released.  Defendant is not to possess any dangerous weapons/firearms/knives.   Court orders a protective order pursuant to 940.47 for Victim A listed in the Victim Identification Key.  Court further orders the protective order to be sealed.

01:28 PM Defendant Jose Luis Aguayo Gutierrez in court, in custody, with attorney Ricardo Tapia.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern Niki Kane appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant is eligible for State Public Defender representation.  An attorney will be appointed.  Preliminary Hearing requested.  PRELIMINARY HEARING REQUESTED WITHIN 10 DAYS.  Victim A appears in Court and is asking for contact with the defendant such as phone contact and visits while the defendant is in custody.  The State objects to any modification of bail and believes a no contact order is appropriate.  Attorney Tapia notes the defendant is unable to post bail and would like the Court to take that into consideration when making a decision on the request to lift the no contact order.  For reasons stated on the record, the Court denies the request to lift the no contact order.  Bail remains as fixed, although, the Court will modify the conditions of bail to include the DNA language.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 10, 2022 at 10:15 am.
